---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use — Quvii Blog"
  description="Terms of use for Quvii."
>
  <div class="container-page py-14 lg:py-20 max-w-3xl prose-pm">
  <h1 class="text-ink">Terms of Use</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-body-faint">Last updated: 2026-05-14</p>

  <div class="prose-pm max-w-prose">
    <p>
      These terms cover the editorial blog at
      <code>quvii.com/blog</code>. The Quvii product itself
      (account creation, image generation, team management, billing)
      is governed by the separate
      <a href="https://quvii.com/terms">Quvii Terms of Service</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Editorial content</h2>
    <p>
      Articles are AI-assisted, reviewed for factual accuracy, and
      cross-referenced against official platform documentation where
      possible. Platform policies (Amazon, Shopify, Etsy, TikTok Shop)
      change frequently — always verify time-sensitive details
      (pixel specs, fees, listing policies) on the official platform
      before acting.
    </p>

    <h2>2. No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      Editorial content is provided "as is." Quvii is not liable
      for losses (listing rejections, lost sales, time) resulting from
      following any guide here. We are not lawyers, tax advisors, or
      official representatives of any marketplace.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Trademarks</h2>
    <p>
      Amazon, Shopify, Etsy, TikTok Shop, Photoroom, Canva, and other
      product names referenced in articles are the property of their
      respective owners. Quvii is an independent SaaS and is not
      affiliated with any of these platforms.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>
      You may link to and quote from articles with attribution. You
      may not mass-scrape, frame, or rebrand content. Automated
      requests must respect <code>robots.txt</code>.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      Terms can change without prior notice. The "Last updated" date
      at the top reflects the current revision.
    </p>
  </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
